ruby-hpricot
------------------------------------------
Hpricot is a fast, flexible HTML parser written in C.  It's designed to 
be very accommodating (like Tanaka Akira's HTree) and to have a very 
helpful library (like some JavaScript libs -- JQuery, Prototype -- give 
you.)  The XPath and CSS parser, in fact, is based on John Resig's 
JQuery.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-7
  ruby-1.8.6-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.8-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  ragel-5.25-1
  rake-0.7.2-1

Canonical website:
  http://code.whytheluckystiff.net/hpricot/

Canonical download:
  http://code.whytheluckystiff.net/dist/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ruby-hpricot-0.6-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ruby-hpricot-0.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ruby-hpricot-0.6-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ruby-hpricot-0.6-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

